    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-10-08T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-10-08T17:00:00-05:00" n="147"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d147">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">822.51/299a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hartman</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-10-08T18:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 8, 1920—6 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>35. A. F. Lindberg is proceeding to Ecuador as the representative of Brown
                    Brothers and the Mercantile Bank of the Americas. Department has been advised by
                    Brown Brothers of their negotiations with the Government of Ecuador for
                    conversion of foreign debt. You may afford Lindberg all proper assistance and
                    facilities in his negotiations with the Government.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Davis</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
